su [username] change user ID or become supre user


- used an env

-c specify command to be executed

whoami

eg

su - oracle

sudo : execute a command as another user typically the superuser

sudo -l
sudo command
sudo -u root
sudo -u user 

sudo su

sudo su - super user account with root env

sudo su - usaername switch to the username account

sudo -s
sudo -u root -s

change the sudo congif

visudo edit /etc/sudoers file


